				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">We'd have to minimize this, obviously. a 6x9 character would take 5400 different tiles according to that math, and that's just not happening. For one thing, I see quick attack and strong attack. We could do away with those. Also, it's not really the frames that count as the space eaters. It's the tiles. We can store tile mappings of the characters for each move in ROM and re-use lots of the tile data. Every character would be given a limited amount of graphical data. What should this limit be? 4k? 8k? 6k? We'll be using bankswitched CHR ROM, right?</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
